  "doc_id": "36342",
  "text": "As mentioned previously, a limited number of prepurified detergent-solubilized G-protein-coupled receptors and model proteins such as bR have been reconstituted into NLPs using various lipids, DMPC alone (2), 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoylphosphatidylcholine alone [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , or a mixture of 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoylphosphatidylcholine and 1-palmitoyl-2-oleoylphosphatidylglycerol (6). Using our cell-free based approach, detergents could be avoided by using single step addition of lipids and other molecules important to protein function. The advantages realized from this single step assembly of integral membrane proteins will expand the repertoire of applications for cell-free protein expression and lead to high throughput production of properly folded soluble membrane proteins supported by a nanolipoprotein particle. ",
